<fieldset> </fieldset>

legend
------
which provides a title for that bordered form.
<legend> </legend>

label
-----
which provides name for particular input using for attribute.
    for:-  it is used to add a ID of input box so when user click on the label it will highlight the particular input box.

    Syntax:-  <label for="id of input"></label>


    note:- form and fieldset tags are block level elements and remaining all are inline level elements. Except input tag all are paired tags.

Input
-----
this tag is used to to enter the user data or which creates a space to enter the particular data.

it has 3 attributes

1. type --> which is used to specify the type of input or data. 
        values for type attribute:- 
                text, password, date, maonth, color, file, number, URL, range, radio, checkbox, submit, hidden.

2. name --> which stores the particular input values with the name of input in database.

3. id --> which used to connect with label.

other attributes

readonly, placeholder, values, autofocus, size, nimlength, maxlength, hidden, disabled.


button
------
which creates a button which can clickable. 
<button> </button>


Textarea
----------
it is alternative for input which takes large number of input.

attributes of textarea
----------------------

1. name --> which stores the particular input values with the name of input in database.

2. id --> which used to connect with label.

3. cols and rows --> used to expand the number of rows and columns of a textarea

<textarea name="" id="" cols="" rows=""> </textarea>

